<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>V1.0<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Fiona Makowski<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Review and Approved</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Contents</p>\r\n<p>DOCUMENT CONTROL<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>1</p>\r\n<p>About This Document<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>Document Control<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>Document History<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>1.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Introduction, Purpose Scope &amp; Users<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Control of Internal Documents<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>4.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document Control<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>5.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document Approval<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>6.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Publishing &amp; Distributing Documents; Withdrawal from Use<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>5</p>\r\n<p>7.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document Updates<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>6</p>\r\n<p>8.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Records Control<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>6</p>\r\n<p>9.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Control of Public Documents<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>7</p>\r\n<p>10.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Documents of external origin<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>7</p>\r\n<p>11.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Managing Records kept on the basis of this document<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>7</p>\r\n<p>12.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Validity and Document Management<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>7</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&emsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Introduction, Purpose Scope &amp; Users</p>\r\n<p>This document is intended to document the standard operating procedures (SOP) at FNQH Pathology for Document Control and details the processes, steps, and detailed instructions so that the relevant (authorised) team member can carry out the task correctly every time.</p>\r\n<p>2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Control of Internal Documents</p>\r\n<p>Internal documents are all documents created inside the organisation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document formatting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The below subheadings are sections that should be used and adhered to in each template for clear composition. Please use this in life document to identify the layout and placement for how a document template should be created and used for each of the sub heading sections and their values outlined below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span> Document Control&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When creating a document manually the document header must contain the organisation\'s logo and the confidentiality level. The footer contains the document name, current version and date of the document, and number of pages.&nbsp; The Document ID is used to quickly &amp; easily identify documents that are apart of the ISMS. This ID is generated based on the following:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Company Name: FNQH&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>A category type: Process, Policy, Procedure, Job Description, Evidence (e.g. Proc, Pol, Mins)</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Unique reference number: e.g. FNQH-SOP-12345</p>\r\n<p>The Version Number is used to control and understand the adaptation and status of a new or in life document.</p>\r\n<p>Date of Version states the date that the document was last edited/updated.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Created By states the individual person who initiated and drafted the original document.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Approved By states the individual person who authorised the documents initial creation in line with the original Created By documents&rsquo; owner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Confidentiality Level - Documents that have a higher confidentiality level, for which the distribution needs to be limited, are published by the document owner and stored on restricited access SharePoint page relevant to the distribution list.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document Approval&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>All new and major release documents are to be submitted for approval by the Lead Pathologist, or in the absence of the Lead Pathologist, by the most senior executive.</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Some documents may require review before approval by one or more designated reviewers who have an interest in, or competence about, the document content.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Please reference sub heading Document Control under Document Formatting to understand the differences in Version Numbers and how they are formed/determined.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Minor Release &ndash; All new minor releases are deemed as pre-approved for immediate release by the author who makes changes to the document. These do not need to go through any additional formal authorisation process so long as the author adheres to the Document Control procedure that keeps the Change History and Version Number up to date across all areas of the document that reflect these values.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>ALL documents that move through the Document Approval process are NOT permitted to have the final &lsquo;Approved by&rsquo; person the same as the &lsquo;Created by&rsquo; person. The final authorising officer must be different to that of the person who initially created the document coming from an unbiased view.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Publishing &amp; Distributing Documents; Withdrawal from Use&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drafts - Any documents that are being drafted and are a current work in progress will remain in the &ldquo;working&rdquo; section or folder in the FNQH Pathology folder whilst the author continues to edit the non-live document.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ready For Review - Any document that is ready to be reviewed for clearance by an approved member of the FNQH senior management team will be moved and remain sitting in this folder or section until the document has been approved or rejected by the appropriate parties.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Clearance Authorised - Once a document has been authorised as ready for clearance by an appropriate authorised party, they will move the accepted document into production with the old document version (if existent) retired.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Archive - The Archive section or folder is where old versions of documents are moved to once they are retired and moved out of production. Old versions of documents are to remain here as a reference point should they need to be referred back to in future.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document Updates&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The person listed as document owner has the responsibility for updating the document. Updates are performed in line with the frequency defined for each document, but at least once a year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All changes to the document must be described briefly in the \"Change History\" table.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>8.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Records Control&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Each internal document must define how records resulting from the use of such a document should be managed; i.e., it must specify the following:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(1) record title,&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(2) storage location,&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(3) person responsible for storage,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(4) controls for record protection, and&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(5) retention time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Employees of the organisation may access stored records only after obtaining permission from the person designated as the person responsible for storing individual records. If the sensitivity of certain records is such that permission for access must be obtained from a different person, this must be stated in the concerned internal document in the chapter describing records control. Access and retrieval rights for records are determined by the owners of individual records. Senior Leadership is responsible for destroying all records for which the retention time has expired.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>9.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Control of Public Documents&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The format and management of Public Documents are to follow the exact same standards and regulations as all those mentioned above outlined under the key heading &ldquo;Control Of Internal, Confidential &amp; Unclassified Documents&rdquo;. The only exclusions to these procedures and practices are the following:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;Document Control&rdquo; section MUST be removed completely from any document that is classified as &ldquo;PUBLIC&rdquo;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;Change History&rdquo; section MUST be removed completely from any document that is classified as &ldquo;PUBLIC&rdquo;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>10.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Documents of external origin&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>External Document Control&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Each external document that is necessary for the planning and operation must be recorded in the appropriate database e.g. Pathhub, SharePoint, Customer Contracts (if applicable).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The person who receives such external documents through regular mail or as courier parcels must forward them to Office manager who must make a record.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span> Managing Records kept on the basis of this document</p>\r\n<p>All records supporting this policy shall be kept in the FNQH Pathology document management system in the location, or system based, indicated in the procedure document. Any additional or deleted records shall be kept account of in the FNQH Pathology logging system such that any future enquiry will be able to clearly identify when the changes occurred, who made them, what these changes were and how the changes were approved.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Validity and Document Management</p>\r\n<p>This document is valid from the date of its approval and will be reviewed on an annual basis. The current working copy will be identified as such, and any superseded documents will be archived and maintained for a period of five years.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>New versions will be identified with a versioning number. Full integers will denote a major document version, and a decimal number will indicate minor amendments or edits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'',	'FNQH - Digital first, better patient outcomes',	0,	'',	'',	0,	0,	453,	'2022-09-07 15:16:17'),
