&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Contents</p>\r\n<p>Corrective and Preventative Action Policy<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>1</p>\r\n<p>About This Document<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>Document Control<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>Document History<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>2</p>\r\n<p>1.1.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Introduction, Purpose Scope &amp; Users<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>1.2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Corrective and Prevenative Action Policy<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>4</p>\r\n<p>2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Supporting Documents<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>5</p>\r\n<p>3.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Managing Records kept on the basis of this document<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>5</p>\r\n<p>4.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Validity and Document Management<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>5</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&emsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.1.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Introduction, Purpose Scope &amp; Users</p>\r\n<p>This document is intended to document the policy at FNQH Pathology for Corrective and Preventative Action.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Corrective and Prevenative Action Policy&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In line with NATA and ISO 15189 requirements, FNQH Pathology will take corrective action to eliminate</p>\r\n<p>the causes of identified nonconformities and ensure the following procedures are adhered to via the following activities &ndash;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Internal and external reviews</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Quality Assurance&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Continuous Improvement</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Informal and formal feedback&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reviewing nonconformities;</p>\r\n<p>Determining the root causes of ISO 15189 ASSESSMENT WORKSHEET Self-assessment</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Assigned staff responsible for corrective and preventative actions must -&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Observe&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Document observations</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Evaluating the need for corrective action to ensure that nonconformities do not recur;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Determine and implement corrective action if&nbsp; needed</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Record and review the results of corrective in the corrective action register&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the purposes of this policy, preventative actions include but are not limited to the following &ndash;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Ensure needed improvements and potential sources of nonconformities are identified and action plans developed,</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Implemented and monitored, using control to ensure they are effective and that the documented procedure</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Minimum annual review information to determine potential nonconformities to determine the root cause; and evaluate the need for preventive action</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Implement preventive action and record the result of the outcome and action taken.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Supporting Documents</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>NATA ISO 15189 ASSESSMENT WORKSHEET Self-assessment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull;<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>https://nata.com.au/files/2021/05/ISO-15189-Assessment-Worksheet-For-Laboratory-use.pdf</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Managing Records kept on the basis of this document</p>\r\n<p>All records supporting this policy shall be kept in the FNQH document management system in the location, or system based, indicated in the procedure document. Any additional or deleted records shall be kept account of in the FNQH logging system such that any future enquiry will be able to clearly identify when the changes occurred, who made them, what these changes were and how the changes were approved.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>Validity and Document Management</p>\r\n<p>This document is valid from the date of its approval and will be reviewed on an annual basis. The current working copy will be identified as such, and any superseded documents will be archived and maintained for a period of five years.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>New versions will be identified with a versioning number. Full integers will denote a major document version, and a decimal number will indicate minor amendments or edits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'',	'FNQH - Digital first, better patient outcomes',	0,	'',	'',	0,	0,	453,	'2022-09-07 15:33:11'),
